<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4336888>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 7. —Thoracic sternum and frontal view: A-D, Gecarcinus ruricola (Linnaeus, 1758), ♂ 55.0× 76.0 mm, Cuba, MNHN-IU-2017-8392 (= MNHN-B13155); E-H, Gecarcoidea lalandii H. Milne Edwards, 1837, ♂ 52.0 × 73.3 mm, Papua New Guinea, MNHN-IU-2013-13254: A, E: thoracic sternum (brushed) with pleon; B, F, thoracic sternum (brushed) without pleon; C, G: genital region with gonopore and penis, D, H, front, proepistome, cephalic appendages, orbit and mxp3. Scale bars: 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4336888/files/figure.png" .

